S-nail is maintained and developed by Steffen Nurpmeso.
This software originates in the codebase of Heirloom mailx, formerly
known as nail, which itself is based upon Berkeley Mail that has
a history back to 1978, and which has been written to replace Unix
mail, a program that already shipped with First Edition Unix.

Other people contributed by reporting problems, suggesting various
improvements, whether directly or indirectly, or submitting actual
code.  Here is a list of those people.  I hope the list is
complete and free of errors.

